reviewText: I think Angelina Ballerina is adorable and she really sparkles in this DVD.  Now even though I have boys, they actually enjoyed it and wouldn't let me turn it off.  There are boys though in the show but I do think it is geared more towards girls.  My boys loved though all the different dances and music.  I liked the whole Nutcracker theme.  In this DVD, Angelina shows how to share, practice, and not eat so many sweets!  The animation is bright and colorful and definitely great to get in the holiday mood!

reviewText: This is a nice companion to The Nutcracker Suite for young children. I like that it shows a blend of pre and post production, as well as the actual on stage performance. It is difficult to convey to children that even in a realm of putting on a fantastic ballet, it's not a perfect process. There is hard work, emotions get triggered, relationships get bumpy. Setbacks and mis-steps happen. In the end, you accept the bumps and find the sweetness and joy in whatever you're doing.
